      "content": "that makes sense for the blog post. it's a really compelling way to look at it. most people just assume regulation is necessary, but when you look at it through that lens, it feels like the only logical conclusion for a truly free society. do you think there's any way for someone to argue that regulation is actually \"good\" without basically admitting they want to control what people think?",
